last_episode_to_air.name: Hearts on Fire
last_episode_to_air.overview: As Gus's life hangs in the balance, Billie turns to Marc for emotional support. Is he just being a good friend, or has he become more than that? Meanwhile, the Nortons are confronting the possible downfall of their business empire.

name: The Secret Daughter
overview: A part-time country pub singer has a chance meeting with a wealthy city hotelier which triggers a series of events that will change her life forever. Explore the worlds of 'the haves' and 'the have nots' with heart, humour, romance and music.

episodes.name: Flame Trees
episodes.overview: Finding herself in hot water with the local hood, Billie pretends to be the secret daughter of Jack Norton in order to escape town, which suddenly lands her in the middle of a grieving family.

episodes.name: Stuck in the Middle with You
episodes.overview: Billie meets with a mixed reception from the Norton family, although Jamie supports her fully-which only complicates her burgeoning crush on him. As Billie wonders how long she can keep up the charade, the family gives her a DNA test to take.

episodes.name: Where Do I Belong?
episodes.overview: After finding out the results of the DNA test, Billie tries to find her place in life.

episodes.name: Lean on Me
episodes.overview: Layla arrives as a sign of support for her best friend, Billie, only to become increasingly close with Jamie.

episodes.name: I Fought The Law
episodes.overview: The preparations for the re-launch of Jack's Bar are overshadowed by Billie's impending court appearance, as jail time becomes a likely outcome.

episodes.name: Risk It
episodes.overview: Still reeling from Harriet's confession, Billie is forced to step up as the headliner for the bar relaunch after their big act pulls out. As Susan preys on her sense of guilt, Billie faces the biggest personal and professional risks of her life.

episodes.name: Always On My Mind
episodes.overview: After turning her back on the Nortons and a record deal, Billie is desperate to connect with her real family. So Gus takes her to visit her mother's sister, where she makes a discovery that upends her life once again.

episodes.name: Respect
episodes.overview: Devastated to learn she's cost the Norton Hotel a very important guest, Billie does everything she can to woo the man back while also dealing with a bizarre meeting at her record label.

episodes.name: Rear View Mirror
episodes.overview: Billie is finally having some good luck in the city: she has her own apartment, a role with the hotel, and a recording contract. But when Billie and Layla are asked to return to Walperinga and perform as part of their old band, will the impromptu trip throw her hard-won success off-balance?

episodes.name: Just Another Love Song
episodes.overview: Billie is thrilled when offered the chance to collaborate with a famous music producer, but her lack of romantic experience hinders her ability to write the love song. When Gus is rushed to the hospital, Billie realizes she must be true to her own voice.

episodes.name: 20 Good Reasons
episodes.overview: With Gus facing life-threatening surgery, Billie puts her music career on hold. But that incites a dilemma-she promised Marc she would perform at his launch party, and she is torn over what to do. Further complicating matters, she learns of a dodgy business deal that threatens the hotel.

episodes.name: Hearts on Fire
episodes.overview: As Gus's life hangs in the balance, Billie turns to Marc for emotional support. Is he just being a good friend, or has he become more than that? Meanwhile, the Nortons are confronting the possible downfall of their business empire.
